{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012xy2rr5bqz6nnpbfS3bjfg","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * Deterministic wallet-funding helper for local E2E tests.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Generates fixed keypairs from seed bytes so tests are reproducible,\n     5→ * then airdrops SOL and confirms before tests run.\n     6→ */\n     7→import {\n     8→  Connection,\n     9→  Keypair,\n    10→  LAMPORTS_PER_SOL,\n    11→  PublicKey,\n    12→} from \"@solana/web3.js\";\n    13→\n    14→// --- Deterministic keypairs ---\n    15→// Fixed 32-byte seeds produce the same keypairs on every run.\n    16→const SEED_PLAYER_A = new Uint8Array(32).fill(0xaa);\n    17→const SEED_PLAYER_B = new Uint8Array(32).fill(0xbb);\n    18→\n    19→export const PLAYER_A = Keypair.fromSeed(SEED_PLAYER_A);\n    20→export const PLAYER_B = Keypair.fromSeed(SEED_PLAYER_B);\n    21→\n    22→/** Default RPC URL for local test validator. */\n    23→export const LOCAL_RPC_URL = \"http://127.0.0.1:8899\";\n    24→\n    25→/** Default airdrop amount per wallet (10 SOL). */\n    26→const DEFAULT_AIRDROP_SOL = 10;\n    27→\n    28→/**\n    29→ * Airdrop SOL to a single wallet and confirm the transaction.\n    30→ *\n    31→ * @param connection - Solana RPC connection\n    32→ * @param to - Public key to fund\n    33→ * @param solAmount - Amount in SOL (default: 10)\n    34→ */\n    35→export async function fundWallet(\n    36→  connection: Connection,\n    37→  to: PublicKey,\n    38→  solAmount = DEFAULT_AIRDROP_SOL,\n    39→): Promise<void> {\n    40→  const lamports = solAmount * LAMPORTS_PER_SOL;\n    41→  const sig = await connection.requestAirdrop(to, lamports);\n    42→  const { blockhash, lastValidBlockHeight } =\n    43→    await connection.getLatestBlockhash();\n    44→  await connection.confirmTransaction(\n    45→    { signature: sig, blockhash, lastValidBlockHeight },\n    46→    \"confirmed\",\n    47→  );\n    48→}\n    49→\n    50→/**\n    51→ * Fund both test players on the local validator.\n    52→ * Call this in a `beforeAll` or global setup before the E2E suite starts.\n    53→ *\n    54→ * @param rpcUrl - RPC endpoint (default: local validator)\n    55→ * @param solAmount - SOL to airdrop per player (default: 10)\n    56→ */\n    57→export async function fundTestWallets(\n    58→  rpcUrl = LOCAL_RPC_URL,\n    59→  solAmount = DEFAULT_AIRDROP_SOL,\n    60→): Promise<{ playerA: Keypair; playerB: Keypair; connection: Connection }> {\n    61→  const connection = new Connection(rpcUrl, \"confirmed\");\n    62→\n    63→  await Promise.all([\n    64→    fundWallet(connection, PLAYER_A.publicKey, solAmount),\n    65→    fundWallet(connection, PLAYER_B.publicKey, solAmount),\n    66→  ]);\n    67→\n    68→  // Sanity-check: verify balances are present\n    69→  const [balA, balB] = await Promise.all([\n    70→    connection.getBalance(PLAYER_A.publicKey),\n    71→    connection.getBalance(PLAYER_B.publicKey),\n    72→  ]);\n    73→\n    74→  const minExpected = solAmount * LAMPORTS_PER_SOL;\n    75→  if (balA < minExpected) {\n    76→    throw new Error(\n    77→      `Player A funding failed: expected >= ${minExpected} lamports, got ${balA}`,\n    78→    );\n    79→  }\n    80→  if (balB < minExpected) {\n    81→    throw new Error(\n    82→      `Player B funding failed: expected >= ${minExpected} lamports, got ${balB}`,\n    83→    );\n    84→  }\n    85→\n    86→  return { playerA: PLAYER_A, playerB: PLAYER_B, connection };\n    87→}\n    88→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"610aad72-d9dc-40e7-807d-09548f27772e","uuid":"891be46c-7b2f-482b-beca-a48edce826e1","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/local/helpers/wallets.ts","content":"/**\n * Deterministic wallet-funding helper for local E2E tests.\n *\n * Generates fixed keypairs from seed bytes so tests are reproducible,\n * then airdrops SOL and confirms before tests run.\n */\nimport {\n  Connection,\n  Keypair,\n  LAMPORTS_PER_SOL,\n  PublicKey,\n} from \"@solana/web3.js\";\n\n// --- Deterministic keypairs ---\n// Fixed 32-byte seeds produce the same keypairs on every run.\nconst SEED_PLAYER_A = new Uint8Array(32).fill(0xaa);\nconst SEED_PLAYER_B = new Uint8Array(32).fill(0xbb);\n\nexport const PLAYER_A = Keypair.fromSeed(SEED_PLAYER_A);\nexport const PLAYER_B = Keypair.fromSeed(SEED_PLAYER_B);\n\n/** Default RPC URL for local test validator. */\nexport const LOCAL_RPC_URL = \"http://127.0.0.1:8899\";\n\n/** Default airdrop amount per wallet (10 SOL). */\nconst DEFAULT_AIRDROP_SOL = 10;\n\n/**\n * Airdrop SOL to a single wallet and confirm the transaction.\n *\n * @param connection - Solana RPC connection\n * @param to - Public key to fund\n * @param solAmount - Amount in SOL (default: 10)\n */\nexport async function fundWallet(\n  connection: Connection,\n  to: PublicKey,\n  solAmount = DEFAULT_AIRDROP_SOL,\n): Promise<void> {\n  const lamports = solAmount * LAMPORTS_PER_SOL;\n  const sig = await connection.requestAirdrop(to, lamports);\n  const { blockhash, lastValidBlockHeight } =\n    await connection.getLatestBlockhash();\n  await connection.confirmTransaction(\n    { signature: sig, blockhash, lastValidBlockHeight },\n    \"confirmed\",\n  );\n}\n\n/**\n * Fund both test players on the local validator.\n * Call this in a `beforeAll` or global setup before the E2E suite starts.\n *\n * @param rpcUrl - RPC endpoint (default: local validator)\n * @param solAmount - SOL to airdrop per player (default: 10)\n */\nexport async function fundTestWallets(\n  rpcUrl = LOCAL_RPC_URL,\n  solAmount = DEFAULT_AIRDROP_SOL,\n): Promise<{ playerA: Keypair; playerB: Keypair; connection: Connection }> {\n  const connection = new Connection(rpcUrl, \"confirmed\");\n\n  await Promise.all([\n    fundWallet(connection, PLAYER_A.publicKey, solAmount),\n    fundWallet(connection, PLAYER_B.publicKey, solAmount),\n  ]);\n\n  // Sanity-check: verify balances are present\n  const [balA, balB] = await Promise.all([\n    connection.getBalance(PLAYER_A.publicKey),\n    connection.getBalance(PLAYER_B.publicKey),\n  ]);\n\n  const minExpected = solAmount * LAMPORTS_PER_SOL;\n  if (balA < minExpected) {\n    throw new Error(\n      `Player A funding failed: expected >= ${minExpected} lamports, got ${balA}`,\n    );\n  }\n  if (balB < minExpected) {\n    throw new Error(\n      `Player B funding failed: expected >= ${minExpected} lamports, got ${balB}`,\n    );\n  }\n\n  return { playerA: PLAYER_A, playerB: PLAYER_B, connection };\n}\n","numLines":88,"startLine":1,"totalLines":88}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_018PBPWCzYrAoaCys7VhGcw9","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the full picture. The key challenge is: the WalletProvider switches between MockWalletProvider and RealWalletProvider based on `VITE_MOCK_MODE`. But for local E2E tests, we need `TestWalletProvider` with specific keypairs.\n\nLooking at the local config, it sets `VITE_MOCK_MODE: \"false\"` which means RealWalletProvider would be used. But for E2E tests, we need TestWalletProvider.\n\nThere must be a way to inject the test keypair. Let me think about how this could work:\n\n\nI could add a `VITE_TEST_WALLET_MODE` environment variable to switch the WalletProvider to use TestWalletProvider, or use Playwright's `addInitScript` to inject the keypair seed directly into the window object, or build test wallet mode directly into the WalletProvider itself. Looking at how the fixture should work, it seems like it needs to create two separate instances or configurations.\n\nFor the dual-browser-context fixture, I'm focusing on the Playwright setup: creating two isolated browser contexts with their own pages, then injecting the keypair seed through something like `window.__TEST_KEYPAIR_SEED__` so the app can detect test mode and use the appropriate wallet provider. The WalletProvider would need modification to recognize this test mode, though that might be handled elsewhere or in a separate task. I need to focus on the fixture itself rather than getting sidetracked by WalletProvider integration—that's a separate concern. The fixture should create two isolated browser contexts with associated keypairs for player A and B, and I'll handle the keypair injection into the page context via `addInitScript()` so the app can access it from the window object. need a way for the app to know it's running in test mode and for each browser context to receive a different keypair. I'll add a `VITE_TEST_WALLET`